QLAC — a low-latency lossless audio codec
Author and maintainer: Leonardo Severi <dev.leosev@gmail.com>

QLAC is derived from the FLAC reference implementation (libFLAC 1.5.0).
It combines files derived from libFLAC with original QLAC code. The
FLAC-derived files retain their original copyright and are used under the
Xiph.Org BSD-like license (see COPYING.Xiph). Modifications to those
files and all original QLAC code are Copyright (C) 2025 Leonardo Severi
and are licensed under the 3-clause BSD license (see COPYING.QLAC). See
LICENSE for how the two bodies of code are combined and which license
applies to each source file.

========================================================================
FLAC contributors (upstream)
========================================================================

The following credits are retained from the FLAC project for the code
QLAC derives from. This list is not exhaustive; for a complete FLAC
contribution history run `git shortlog -s` / `git log` on the upstream
FLAC repository or visit https://gitlab.xiph.org/xiph/flac and
https://github.com/xiph/flac/commits

Original author: Josh Coalson <jcoalson@users.sourceforge.net>
Maintainer 2012-2020: Erik de Castro Lopo <erikd@mega-nerd.com>
Maintainer from 2022: Martijn van Beurden <mvanb1@gmail.com>

Copyright (C) 2000-2009  Josh Coalson
Copyright (C) 2011-2025  the Xiph.Org Foundation

Website : https://www.xiph.org/flac/

Other major contributors and their contributions:

"lvqcl" <lvqcl@users.sourceforge.net>
* Visual Studio build system.
* Optimisations in the encoder and decoder.

"Janne Hyvärinen" <cse@sci.fi>
* Visual Studio build system.
* Unicode handling on Windows.

"Andrey Astafiev" <andrei@tvcell.ru>
* Russian translation of the HTML documentation

"Miroslav Lichvar" <lichvarm@phoenix.inf.upol.cz>
* IA-32 assembly versions of several libFLAC routines

"Brady Patterson" <bpat@users.sourceforge.net>
* AIFF file support, PPC assembly versions of libFLAC routines

"Daisuke Shimamura" <Daisuke_Shimamura@nifty.com>
* i18n support in the XMMS plugin

"X-Fixer" <x-fixer@narod.ru>
* Configuration system, tag editing, and file info in the Winamp2 plugin

"Matt Zimmerman" <mdz@debian.org>
* Libtool/autoconf/automake make system, flac man page
